wikipedia_page.main: Ernest Stanley Wilcockson (11 May 1905 – 3 March 1965) was an English professional footballer who played as a half-back in the Football League for Crystal Palace, York City, Leeds United and Swindon Town in non-League football for Crittall Athletic, Dartford and Tunbridge Wells Rangers. After retiring he worked as a coach with West Ham United's youth team.
